</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,908,1151]" box="[199,1045,944,971]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,944,971]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Distribution.</emphasis>
Europe; also North Africa. 
<collectingCountry box="[663,762,945,971]" name="Portugal" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: four northern provinces.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,908,1151]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,981,1007]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Ecology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dolichopodinae" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1817" box="[307,571,982,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="germanus">
<emphasis box="[307,571,982,1007]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Hercostomus germanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recorded from most macrohabitat categories in 
<collectingCountry box="[1214,1312,981,1007]" name="Portugal" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Portugal</collectingCountry>
, except for the littoral zone and the dunes. In northwestern and central Europe, it is mainly found on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lindley" authorityYear="1830" box="[1164,1268,1017,1043]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Apiaceae</taxonomicName>
(often 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Daucus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="carota">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Daucus carota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in sunny sites along trails in open forests (
<bibRefCitation author="Pollet, M." box="[711,846,1053,1079]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 190" refId="ref34362" refString="Pollet, M. (2000) A documented Red List of the dolichopodid flies (Diptera: Dolichopodidae) of Flanders [in Dutch with English summary]. Communications of the Institute of Nature Conservation, 8, 1 - 190." type="journal article" year="2000">Pollet 2000</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,908,1151]" box="[199,763,1088,1115]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1088,1115]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
8.0 (fairly rare). Extremely rare (FL).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,908,1151]" box="[199,795,1124,1151]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,386,1124,1151]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Activity period.</emphasis>
May–September, with peak in June.
</paragraph>
